result.execSummary:
The defendant Cedric Dewayne Greer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cedric Dewayne Greer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cedric Dewayne Greer was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cedric Dewayne Greer in court with attorney Odalo Joseph Ohiku.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Letter of verification of community service filed and reviewed.  Court orders sentence to be permanently stayed.

Defendant Cedric Dewayne Greer in court with attorney Odalo Joseph Ohiku.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have resolved matter.  Pursuant to negotiations, count 4 is DISMISSED and as to count 3:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.
Sentencint proceeded.  Statements by all parties.  The court sentences the defendant to serve 30 days House of Correction, credit for 6 days time served.  The court will STAY the sentence until a review date of 2-1-2016 at 8:15.    The court orders defendant to pay all applicable costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, DNA sample and costs by the review date (CASH BAIL ON DEPOSIT TO APPLY) and failure to do so will result in entry of civil judgment.  Defendant is to perform 25 hours of community service at a non-profit charitable organization and provide proof on the review date.  Review hearing scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 08:15 am.

Defendant Cedric Dewayne Greer in court with attorney Odalo Joseph Ohiku.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin. In chambers discussion.  Case called.  The court is informed that the state is unable to proceed as to counts 1 and 2.  Upon motion of the defense the court orders counts 1 and 2 dismissed without prejudice.
Counts 3 and 4 will be re-set for another trial date.   The court will no longer accept any plea bargains or negotiations after today.  Case is adjourned to 10-19-2015 at 8:15 for jury.  Jury trial scheduled for October 19, 2015 at 08:15 am.
